Regarding the date - some things strongly suggests this was not a 1977 show because of a lack of songs like "New Kid In Town" which reached #1 in the charts in 1977. During the show, J.D. Souther mentions that it&#039;s Glenn Frey&#039;s birthday (November 6) - which means they would have performed a full show in late 1977 without playing their number one hit of the year - which just doesn&#039;t make sense. Also, Randy Meisner left the Eagles in September 1977 - which is the month the "Hotel California" tour ended.
